  05 CSS

  Way 01 
we can simply write the css of all the components in the index.css file using the className.
  Limitation:- Suppose we create a component button 
                and also create a component header 
                then we write the css of both using className
                -> when we give the same className of button to the button of the header then it occupy The
                same css of the button component.
                -> If we want to do different css of the button of the header then we cannot do it.  

Way 02 
Here we create a different css file for different components, where we create a button.css,header.css for the 
components (button,header).
But,same error will occur here so we are not prefering this.

You can check the code of the module css.
First we create 2 folders of Header and Button
we create a header.css and button.css.
we wrote the css in both the file.
-> when we try to the className of the button in the button of the header, we cannot able to access it bcz
it was in different module so we can easily style this button using different css. Solved the problem.

